== Yellow Rice ==

In a small #pot, melt @Butter{1%tbsp} over medium heat. Stir in @Turmeric{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings); cook stirring frequently, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, a big pinch of @Salt{pinch}, and @Pepper{}.

Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Prep ==

Meanwhile, bring @Butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @Lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @Tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

== White Sauce ==

In a small #bowl, combine @Sour Cream{1.5%tbsp}, @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @Garlic Powder{1%tsp}, and a squeeze of lemon.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Diced Chicken Thighs{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels; season with @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Pita Wedges ==

Toast @Whole Wheat Pitas{2} until softened and warmed through.

Spread with softened butter, then cut each pita into quarters.

== To Serve ==

Once rice is done, fluff with a #fork; stir in half the scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with chicken and tomato in separate sections; season tomato with a pinch of salt.

Drizzle everything with as much white sauce and @Hot Sauce{1%tsp} as you like; garnish with remaining scallion greens. Serve with pita and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> TIP: We like to scoop up some of the rice, chicken, tomato and sauces with a pita wedge and eat it all in one bite!